CleverDns - Server recursor code
install instructions.

This is made thinking on Ubuntu Server. but the process its similar in every Posixa like system

pre-install: 
you could do this via aptitude or apt-get :)

-pdns-server
-pdns-backend-pipe
-libyaml-tiny-perl 
-libnetaddr-ip-perl
-libnet-dns-perl

install CleverDns:
use git to get all the code of CleverDns

bash$ cd /etc/powedns/
bash$ mkdir /etc/powerdns/cleverdns
bash$ cd /etc/powerdns/

you have already the code if not
go to http://github.com/gagoar/CleverDns/tree/source and hit Download Source,  ask if you want tar or zip (you know the way about thath)
or
do it with git 
bash|/etc/powerdns/$git clone git://github.com/gagoar/CleverDns.git

you will need configurate pdns.conf in order to run as server.

copy the next configuracion in /etc/powerdns/pdns.conf
#############################
config-dir=/etc/powerdns
daemon=yes
disable-axfr=yes
local-address=0.0.0.0
local-port=53
module-dir=/usr/lib/powerdns
setgid=pdns
setuid=pdns
socket-dir=/var/run
version-string=powerdns
include=/etc/powerdns/pdns.d
disable-tcp=yes
distributor-threads=5
logfile=/var/log/pdns.log
loglevel=9
cache-ttl=0
query-cache-ttl=0
no-shuffle=yes
use-logfile=yes
query-logging=no
pipebackend-abi-version=2
launch=pipe
pipe-command=/etc/powerdns/cleverdns/recursor.pl
################################################
post-install:
you have to edit /etc/default/pdns.conf and change START=no with START=yes

running server:
bash$ service pdns start

NOTE: to find it out if cleverdns its working properly... you can do (in ubuntu):
bash$ service pdns monitor 
and it will run in monitor mode,  you will see all the request of the clients hiting Clever and Clever answering back in each case.
